            <title>[JCR-2071] IndexMerger throws null pointer exception without stacktrace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2071</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>I get the following errors in my log file randomly.  It seems to happen most often when creating the lucene indices, but has happened at other times as well:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
[IndexMerger] ERROR - Error while merging indexes: java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The code at org.apache.jackrabbit.core.query.lucene.IndexMerger line 344 appears to be the point where the error is logged, but no other information is provided because the throwable isn&amp;#39;t sent to the log (only the toString() version of the exception).  I haven&amp;#39;t been able to tell if any indexes are corrupt when this happens.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I suggest that the logger be changed to determine where the null pointer is coming from first, then resolve the actual issue that is occurring.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
                <environment>Windows OS (XP, Vista)&lt;br/&gt;
Linux RHEL&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;</environment>
